### aarch64 crt1 for MesCC (NEW) — defines :_start, the ELF entry point.
### Minimal Linux aarch64 startup: call main, then exit(main's return value).
### Uses M2libc's aarch64 macros (LOAD_W16_AHEAD/SKIP_32_DATA/&main/BLR_X16,
### SET_X8_TO_SYS_EXIT/SYSCALL). MesCC labels the entry function :main, and the
### Mes ELF header's e_entry points at :_start, so this is the glue between them.
:_start
	INIT_SP
	LOAD_W16_AHEAD
	SKIP_32_DATA
	&main
	BLR_X16
	SET_X8_TO_SYS_EXIT
	SYSCALL
